RelatedSentence: The BJP will be able to send just one MP from the upcoming three vacancies from Bihar .

The seats of Ram Vilas Paswan , Rajiv Pratap Rudy and Ram Kripal Yadav will be vacant , and if the Janata Dal ( United ) and the Rashtriya Janata Dal reach an understanding , the parties can send two of their representatives to the Upper House .

The seats of Ram Vilas Paswan , Rajiv Pratap Rudy and Ram Kripal Yadav will be vacant , and if the Janata Dal ( United ) and the Rashtriya Janata Dal reach an understanding , the parties can send two of their representatives to the Upper House .
It is learnt that the RJD and JD ( U ) will take the two seats and there will be a contest for the third seat from the State .
Uttarakhand CM Harish Rawat is already facing dissidence from a section of MLAs , and the BJP may use this opportunity to prove its strength in the State .
